The here used version of the NEXMark Generator is a modified version of the NEXMark Benchmark found at http://datalab.cs.pdx.edu/niagara/NEXMark/. Instead of generating XML documents it generates RelationalTuple structures.

The NEXMark Generator simulates an auction house. It generates the streams people, auctions and bids. The auctions are created to static categories.

Configuration:
The configuration can be changed in the NEXMarkGeneratorConfiguration.properties file.

Usage:
The Generator can either be instantiated or used as an external sever.

As an instance:

   1. create and start the server with one of the constructors
    NexmarkServer server = new NexmarkServer(<startPort>);
    NexmarkServer server = new NexmarkServer(<startPort>, <elementLimit>);
    NexmarkServer server = new NexmarkServer(<personPort>, <auctionPort>, <bidPort>, <categoryPort>);
    NexmarkServer server = new NexmarkServer(<personPort>, <auctionPort>, <bidPort>, <categoryPort>, <elementLimit>);
    
    server.start();
    
   2. create a conneciton to the server
    Socket socket = new Socket(<host>, <port>);
    // the <port> specifies the benchmark stream to be recieved 
    // if used locally <host> would be "localhost"
    
    ObjectInputStream in = new ObjectInputStream(s.getInputStream());
    
   3. use the stream
    // the data (RelationalTuples) is now send through the ObjectInputStream
    in.readObject();
    
   4. stop the server when finished
    server.stop();
    
As an external server
    
   1. start the server
    Syntax: java NexmarkServer <ports> [<elementLimit>]
     <ports> can be specified via:
	  -ports|-p <personPort>, <auctionPort>, <bidPort>, <categoryPort> (to specify specific ports)
	  -port_range|-pr <startPort> (to specify a port range, personPort is <startPort>, auctionPort is <startPort> + 1, ...
	  
	 <elementLimit> is an optional parameter to specify an elementLimit. Only <elementLimit> tuple are sent over the stream
	  -element_limit|-el <elementLimit>
	  
	Example:
	    java NexmarkServer -pr 2000 -el 10000    
    
   2. create a conneciton to the server
    Socket socket = new Socket(<host>, <port>);
    ObjectInputStream in = new ObjectInputStream(s.getInputStream());
    
   3. use the stream
    // the data (RelationalTuples) is now send through the ObjectInputStream
    in.readObject();
    